HEADWORD: Hyposulphite
<hw>Hy`po*sul"phite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A salt of what was formerly called hyposulphurous
acid; a thiosulphate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A salt
of hyposulphurous acid proper.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hyposulphuric</ent>⟦br⟧
